# UMCP Repository — AI Coding Instructions
#
# AXIOM-0: "Collapse is generative; only what returns is real."
#
# Full specification: .github/copilot-instructions.md
#
# HARD CONSTRAINTS:
# - Never attribute GCD structures to external theories
#   (IC ≤ F is "integrity bound" not "AM-GM"; S is "Bernoulli field entropy"
#   not "Shannon entropy"; F + ω = 1 is "duality identity" not "unitarity")
# - Never redefine Tier-1 symbols: F, ω, S, C, κ, IC, τ_R, regime
# - Import frozen parameters from src/umcp/frozen_contract.py, never hardcode
# - Three-valued verdicts: CONFORMANT / NONCONFORMANT / NON_EVALUABLE
# - INF_REC = typed string in data, float("inf") in Python
# - No back-edges: Tier-2 cannot modify Tier-0 or Tier-1 within a run
# - Every source file starts with: from __future__ import annotations
# - Line length: 120 chars
#
# AFTER EVERY CODE CHANGE:
#   python scripts/update_integrity.py
#   python scripts/pre_commit_protocol.py
#
# TERMINOLOGY:
#   WRONG → RIGHT
#   Shannon entropy → Bernoulli field entropy
#   AM-GM inequality → Integrity bound (IC ≤ F)
#   AM-GM gap → Heterogeneity gap (Δ = F − IC)
#   rederives/recovers → derives independently
#   unitarity → duality identity F + ω = 1
#   hyperparameter → frozen parameter
#
# TIER SYSTEM:
#   Tier-1: Immutable invariants (F+ω=1, IC≤F, IC≈exp(κ))
#   Tier-0: Protocol (src/umcp/ — validation, kernel, seam, contracts)
#   Tier-2: Closures (closures/ — 13 domains validated through Tier-0)
#
# KEY FILES:
#   src/umcp/frozen_contract.py   — frozen constants, regime classification
#   src/umcp/kernel_optimized.py  — kernel computation (F, ω, S, C, κ, IC)
#   src/umcp/validator.py         — root-file validation
#   src/umcp/seam_optimized.py    — seam budget computation
#   src/umcp/epistemic_weld.py    — epistemic verdict (RETURN/GESTURE/DISSOLUTION)
